<TITLE> Campus arms: Sahara issues dire warning </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)Home minister Sahara Khatun has told parliament that the government will stop armed gangs destabilising educational institutions "at any cost". While issuing a statement on an urgent matter, the minister referred Monday's violence at Dhaka University took place between two factions of opposition BNP's student front Jatiyatabadi Chhatra Dal over positions in the central committee. Witnesses said pro-ruling party Chhatra League was also involved in the violence. She said the government was committed to maintaining peaceful atmosphere at all educational institutions. "We don't want to see any armed cadre entering Dhaka University," Khatun told parliament. "Measures will be taken to curb those who are out to destabilise the peaceful academic atmosphere by creating unrest at Dhaka University," she said. "The government will maintain congenial atmosphere at all educational institutions at any cost," she said. The minister said Monday's campus violence harmed the common students coming from far and wide of the country.
